## Build & Test

```bash
cd solracer-program
anchor build

# Run existing tests first to confirm nothing broke
anchor test

# Then write new tests for:
# - delegate_session creates PDA correctly
# - submit_result works with session key signer
# - submit_result works with wallet signer (backward compat)
# - submit_result rejects expired session
# - submit_result rejects wrong session key
# - claim_prize works with session key
# - funds go to player_wallet not session_key
```

---

## Discriminators needed on Windows side

After `anchor build`, run this to get the new discriminator for `delegate_session`:

```bash
node -e "
const crypto = require('crypto');
const d = crypto.createHash('sha256').update('global:delegate_session').digest();
console.log('delegate_session:', JSON.stringify(Array.from(d.slice(0,8))));
"
```

> Copy this output  it's needed in [backend-ts/src/services/program.ts](file:///d:/mislanious/Unity/Uinty_projects/Solracer/backend-ts/src/services/program.ts) and [ErLifecycleManager.cs](file:///d:/mislanious/Unity/Uinty_projects/Solracer/client-unity/Assets/Scripts/Network/ErLifecycleManager.cs).

---

## Deploy

```bash
anchor deploy --provider.cluster devnet
```

> The program ID stays the same (`5Qe7B4LEMjmfbWgt2ctKY8ZzesDobubBi79HwPABJFkQ`) as long as you have the keypair. Confirm with `solana program show <PROGRAM_ID>`.
